I did not come to Congress seeking impeachment, nor do I agree with the extreme voices on either side. But we must act to protect our Constitution, the integrity of our elections, and our national security.

Inviting foreign interference in our elections strikes at the heart of our democracy, threatens our security, and is an abuse of power. The President obstructed Congress by withholding evidence, refusing to comply with lawful subpoenas, and prohibiting officials from testifying.
